    <p>LIV­ING ROOM ES­SEN­TIAL</p>
    <p>A good state­ment fur­ni­ture piece fea­tures an el­e­ment of sur­prise. Take the Molly Dresser by Aar­ti­cal, for in­stance. Within its bar-cart sil­hou­ette is an ar­ray of un­ex­pected (yet prac­ti­cal) so­lu­tions: an oval mir­ror, a pull-out drawer, rows of shelves, an LED light strip and built-in USB port and socket. Aar­ti­cal’s Driz­zle Stand­ing Mir­ror also fits the bill, with its unusual teepee-like de­sign and teardrop-shaped mir­ror.</p>
    <p>Mean­while, the Momo Chaise Lounge’s de­light­ful com­bi­na­tion of curvi­lin­ear shapes and cheery hues of yel­low and sky blue is a convo starter. Look­ing for some­thing quirky? The Pint End Ta­ble by Jot­terGoods fea­tures a bird cage­like sil­hou­ette with a brass fin­ish that gives it an Art Deco edge.</p>
    <p>The Mondi For­est Stool can dou­ble as an end ta­ble. Bio­philia is al­ways in trend, too, so its flo­ral green fab­ric is per­fect for ev­ery room in the house.</p>
    <p>Check out homegrown multi-brand fur­ni­ture store Star Liv­ing for more state­ment fur­ni­ture by Star, Mondi, Jot­terGoods and Aar­ti­cal. Visit www.star­liv­ing.com.sg for its list of stores.</p>

